<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-3556] nodetool info reports inaccurate datacenter/rack for localhost</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3556</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The datacenter &amp;amp; rack information provided by &apos;nodetool info&apos; is incorrect when using &apos;nodetool -h localhost info&apos;. This is because the IP address passed to the EndpointSnitch to determine the datacenter &amp;amp; rack is sourced from the host parameter provided to nodetool and not the actual endpoint address used in the ring.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12533581">CASSANDRA-3556</key>
            <summary>nodetool info reports inaccurate datacenter/rack for localhost</summary>
